{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2016-09-01T00:05:16-05:00"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/09-01-feeling-badly-about-saying-no"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"title":"Feeling Badly About Saying No","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/09-01-feeling-badly-about-saying-no","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"I’ve been on a kick lately about saying no to things. Apparently I’ve been pushed to my limit and can’t handle anything else so everything is turning into a no. But I still feel like a jerk for saying no and I don’t like feeling like a jerk. I start to apologize for saying no when I really meant it.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","role":"collection","title":"Brunow"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2016":{"type":"topic","title":"2016","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2016","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016","abstract":[]},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"kind":"article","identifier":